2022 kicked off on a pleasnat note for singer Olakira as he bagged massive endorsement deal with luxury automobile manufacturer, Maserati. The collaboration was informed due to the recognition of his hit track, “In My Maserati” which has continued to receive global acclaim. The video has amassed over 41 million views on YouTube since its release in 2020. Olakira recently paid a visit to the Maserati headquarters and was given a pleasant surprise when their new collaboration was announced.   Ex-wife of Mercy Aigbe’s new boo speaks up     Kayamata seller Jaruma: I’m President-in-waiting     AFCON 2021: Why I stopped watching football – Naira Marley   In a video shared on the brands official Instgaram page, the excited singer noted he didn’t expect the surprise but confessed to loving the brand and privileged to have the collaboration. - Advertisement - The spokesperson of Maserati Middle East in the video said: “We love the song and we love you! It’s an official collaboration as they went on to unveil a Maserati for Olakira. The video’s caption read: If 36 millions views seemed surreal, a real #Maserati collaboration seemed unreal for @iamolakira. On the terms of their collaboration, the singer was given a global endorsement deal which will ensure he has access to Maserati cars in any country he visits. With this, Olakira becomes the first African artiste to enter into a collaboration with the luxury automobile brand.